## Comparative Summary of Reform Strategies

| Reform Strategy                         | Key Benefits                              | Challenges/Considerations                    | Evidence of Effectiveness                      |
|---------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| Eliminate Cash Bail                   | Removes wealth-based detention; reduces jail population | Political resistance; requires alternative mechanisms | NJ: 44% reduction in pretrial jail population ([Grant, 2019](https://www.njcourts.gov/courts/assets/criminaljustice/2018-criminal-justice-reform-report.pdf)) |
| Presumption of Release (ROR)          | Reduces unnecessary detention; maintains court appearance | Judicial discretion variability              | DC: 94% pretrial release, 88% court appearance ([Marshall Project, 2020](https://www.themarshallproject.org/2020/10/30/the-state-of-bail-reform)) |
| Pretrial Support Services             | Addresses barriers to court appearance; improves compliance | Requires funding and infrastructure          | Bail Project: >90% court appearance ([Bail Project, 2021](https://bailproject.org)) |
| Transparent Risk Assessments          | Informs decisions; potential to reduce bias if well-designed | Risk of perpetuating bias; lack of transparency | Mixed results; calls for independent validation ([Stevenson, 2019](https://minnesotalawreview.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Stevenson_MLR.pdf)) |
| Charitable Bail Funds                 | Enables release without financial burden; reduces coercion | Limited scale; sustainability concerns       | Bronx Freedom Fund: 98% court appearance ([Feige, 2015](https://www.themarshallproject.org/2015/06/11/bail-is-unfair-here-s-a-simple-way-to-fix-it)) |
| Legislative Safeguards                | Formalizes reforms; mandates fairness considerations | Enforcement and compliance challenges        | Georgia reforms show mixed compliance ([Beacon Magazine, 2021](https://www.beaconmagazine.com/confronting-race-and-class-in-savannah)) |
| Data Transparency and Accountability | Enables monitoring and continuous improvement | Requires commitment and resources             | Essential for all reforms                       |

